                    <div>
                        <span class="text-xs font-semibold inline-block py-1 px-2 uppercase rounded-full bg-blue-200 text-blue-800">
                            Timeline
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-right">
                        <span id="current-time" class="text-xs font-semibold inline-block text-blue-600">
                            0:00
                        </span> / 
                        <span id="total-time" class="text-xs font-semibold inline-block text-gray-500">
                            3:30
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="overflow-hidden h-2 mb-4 text-xs flex rounded bg-blue-200">
                    <div id="progress-bar" style="width:0%" class="shadow-none flex flex-col text-center whitespace-nowrap text-white justify-center bg-blue-600 transition-all duration-500"></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex justify-center space-x-4">
                <button id="play-pause-btn" class="px-6 py-3 bg-green-600 text-white font-bold rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-green-700 transition duration-300 flex items-center">
                    <svg id="play-icon" class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM9.555 7.168A1 1 0 008 8v4a1 1 0 001.555.832l3-2a1 1 0 000-1.664l-3-2z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                    <svg id="pause-icon" class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 hidden" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zM7 8a1 1 0 012 0v4a1 1 0 11-2 0V8zm5-1a1 1 0 00-1 1v4a1 1 0 102 0V8a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                    <span id="btn-text">Play Simulation</span>
                </button>
                <button id="reset-btn" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-300 text-gray-800 font-bold rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-gray-400 transition duration-300 flex items-center">
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 2a1 1 0 011 1v2.101a7.002 7.002 0 0111.601 2.566 1 1 0 11-1.885.666A5.002 5.002 0 005.9 5.148V7a1 1 0 01-2 0V3a1 1 0 011-1zm4.5 9.5a1 1 0 01-1 1h-2a1 1 0 010-2h.168l1.46-2.583a.997.997 0 011.674 1.15l-1.46 2.583H8.5z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                    Reset
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SCRIPT TRACKER -->
        <div class="p-6 bg-gray-50 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-900">Full Script Flow</h3>
            <div id="script-panel" class="space-y-4">
                <!-- Script steps will be rendered here -->
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <script>
        // Data parsed from the intro_to_ai_insurance_script.md file
        const scriptData = [
            // Timing in seconds (converted to milliseconds later)
            { time: 0, voice: "Welcome. In the insurance sector, Artificial Intelligence is no longer a futuristic concept—it's a present-day mandate. Yet, for many leaders, AI still generates more confusion than value. The core question remains: How do we move AI from small, fragmented pilots to meaningful, company-wide strategic advantage?", visuals: "Branded title card. Clean, executive-level graphics. Subtle background animation showing data streams connecting core business functions." },
            { time: 15, voice: "We must first clarify what we're talking about. Modern AI is a spectrum, not a single technology. At the foundation, we have **Machine Learning**—models that identify patterns and make predictions. This powers basic fraud detection or simple claims triage.", visuals: "Graphic illustrating the 'AI Spectrum' with three tiers: 1. Machine Learning (Prediction). 2. Generative AI (Creation). 3. Agentic AI (Action/Decision)." },
            { time: 30, voice: "Above that is **Generative AI**, which excels at content creation—drafting policy documents, summarizing claim histories, and personalizing marketing emails. But the real game-changer is the emerging field of **Agentic AI**...", visuals: "AI Spectrum graphic remains; Generative AI section highlights." },
            { time: 45, voice: "**Agentic AI** is the future of insurance operations. These are systems designed not just to predict, but to **act and make autonomous decisions**. Think of a virtual underwriter that can autonomously synthesize external data, generate a risk score, and issue a policy offer in minutes, all without human intervention. This shift from **prediction to action** is the essence of digital transformation in our industry.", visuals: 'Visual transition to a simplified animation of an "AI Agent": Inputs (Data streams) -> Processing (Brain/Model) -> Outputs (Decision/Action). Large, pulsing "ACTION" button.' },
            { time: 75, voice: "Historically, insurers have focused AI on cost-centers like customer service or IT. But where does the *outsized* strategic value lie? Our analysis shows a clear answer: **Core Functions.**", visuals: 'Transition to a clean, executive-level chart graphic: Highlighting **Core Functions** as the center of value.' },
            { time: 90, voice: "The biggest difference between AI Leaders and Laggards isn't the amount of money spent; it's the **focus**. Leaders concentrate their investment on complex, high-leverage areas like **Underwriting** and **Product Management**. This is where AI moves from saving pennies on efficiency to multiplying profits on risk selection.", visuals: 'Chart highlighting: **AI Leaders Focus on Core Functions** (Underwriting, Product Management). Large number: 2.1x ROI.' },
            { time: 105, voice: "**For Underwriting:** AI agents replace static rules with dynamic, predictive models, achieving better mortality forecasts and improving placement rates. **For Product Management:** AI analyzes market shifts and competitor data in real-time to suggest and launch highly personalized products faster than ever before.", visuals: 'Visual highlighting the "Underwriting" and "Product Management" sections with brief explanatory text overlays.' },
            { time: 120, voice: "Implementing AI isn't an IT problem; it's a **business ownership problem**. To scale successfully, the C-suite must commit to three pillars:", visuals: 'Visual of three interconnected blue pillars or circles appearing on screen.' },
            { time: 135, voice: "**Pillar 1: Business-Led Mandate.** The accountability for AI outcomes—and the budget—must reside with the business function heads, such as the Chief Underwriting Officer or Head of Claims, not solely with the CIO. They own the P&L impact.", visuals: '**Pillar 1 Label:** Business Ownership. (Pillar 1 illuminates green)' },
            { time: 150, voice: "**Pillar 2: Foundational Stack.** You cannot build complex AI on legacy infrastructure. A move to modular, cloud-native **SaaS Core Systems** is non-negotiable. This provides the data liquidity and agility that AI agents need to operate.", visuals: '**Pillar 2 Label:** Modern SaaS Foundation. (Pillar 2 illuminates green. Icon of cloud server.)' },
            { time: 165, voice: "**Pillar 3: Human Augmentation.** AI is not about replacement; it’s about **augmentation**. We must proactively re-skill our workforce, shifting the human role from data processor to **model governor**—managing the AI, handling exceptions, and ensuring ethical compliance.", visuals: '**Pillar 3 Label:** Workforce Augmentation & Governance. (Pillar 3 illuminates green. Icon of a human and robot working together.)' },
            { time: 180, voice: "The era of AI pilots is over. The competitive advantage belongs to those who view AI as a strategic lever to transform core, high-leverage functions. By focusing on decisive P&L impact, securing business ownership, and building a modern digital foundation, you can move your organization from observing the future of insurance to actively leading it.", visuals: 'Final screen summarizing the three pillars and the core message. Call to action text appears.' },
            { time: 210, voice: "Thank you for joining this introduction.", visuals: 'Fade out to "Thank You" screen and final logo/URL.' }
        ];
        
        const totalDuration = 210; // 3:30 in seconds

        const visualsPanel = document.getElementById('visuals-panel');
        const voiceoverText = document.getElementById('voiceover-text');
        const scriptPanel = document.getElementById('script-panel');
        const progressBar = document.getElementById('progress-bar');
        const currentTimeDisplay = document.getElementById('current-time');
        const statusText = document.getElementById('status-text');
        const playPauseBtn = document.getElementById('play-pause-btn');
        const resetBtn = document.getElementById('reset-btn');
        const playIcon = document.getElementById('play-icon');
        const pauseIcon = document.getElementById('pause-icon');
        const btnText = document.getElementById('btn-text');

        let isPlaying = false;
        let simulationTime = 0; // in seconds
        let intervalId = null;
        let currentSceneIndex = -1;

        // --- Utility Functions ---

        function formatTime(seconds) {
            const min = Math.floor(seconds / 60);
            const sec = Math.floor(seconds % 60);
            return `${min}:${sec.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
        }

        function updateProgress() {
            const percentage = (simulationTime / totalDuration) * 100;
            progressBar.style.width = `${percentage}%`;
            currentTimeDisplay.textContent = formatTime(simulationTime);
        }

        function renderScriptTimeline() {
            scriptPanel.innerHTML = scriptData.map((scene, index) => {
                const isActive = index === currentSceneIndex;
                return `
                    <div id="scene-${index}" class="p-3 rounded-lg border transition-all duration-500 ${isActive ? 'bg-blue-50 border-blue-600 shadow-lg' : 'bg-white border-gray-200'}">
                        <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1">
                            <span class="font-semibold ${isActive ? 'text-blue-800' : 'text-gray-700'}">${formatTime(scene.time)} - Scene ${index + 1}</span>
                            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-500">${scene.visuals.split(' ')[0]}...</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm ${isActive ? 'text-blue-900' : 'text-gray-600'}">${scene.voice.substring(0, 80)}...</p>
                    </div>
                `;
            }).join('');
        }

        function updateScene(index) {
            if (index < 0 || index >= scriptData.length) return;

            currentSceneIndex = index;
            const scene = scriptData[index];
            
            // Update Voiceover
            voiceoverText.innerHTML = scene.voice;
            
            // Update Visuals (using simple structure based on text description)
            let visualContent = '';
            if (index === 0) {
                visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-blue-900 p-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center text-white';
                visualContent = `<h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold">${scene.voice.match(/Title Card:\s*(.*?):/)?.[1] || 'AI for Insurance'}</h2>`;
            } else if (index >= 1 && index <= 3) {
                visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center text-gray-800';
                visualContent = `
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">The AI Spectrum</h3>
                        <div class="flex justify-center space-x-4">
                            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg shadow ${index === 1 ? 'bg-blue-100 font-bold' : 'bg-gray-200'}">1. Machine Learning <span class="text-xs">(Prediction)</span></div>
                            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg shadow ${index === 2 ? 'bg-blue-100 font-bold' : 'bg-gray-200'}">2. Generative AI <span class="text-xs">(Creation)</span></div>
                            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg shadow ${index === 3 ? 'bg-green-100 font-bold pulse-animation' : 'bg-gray-200'}">3. Agentic AI <span class="text-xs">(Action/Decision)</span></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                `;
            } else if (index === 4) {
                 visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-green-700 p-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center text-white pulse-animation';
                 visualContent = `
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h3 class="text-4xl font-extrabold">AGENTIC AI</h3>
                        <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-2xl space-x-2">
                           <span>PREDICTION</span>
                           <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-yellow-300 animate-bounce" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
                           <span class="font-mono text-yellow-300">ACTION</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-lg mt-4">Autonomous Decisions (e.g., Virtual Underwriter)</div>
                    </div>
                 `;
            } else if (index >= 5 && index <= 7) {
                visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-white p-6 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center text-gray-800 border-2 border-blue-500';
                visualContent = `
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 ${index >= 6 ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-red-700'}">Strategic Value: ${index >= 6 ? 'CORE FUNCTIONS' : 'COST CENTERS'}</h3>
                        <div class="flex justify-around text-center space-x-4">
                            <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-red-100 shadow flex-1 ${index < 6 ? 'border-4 border-red-500' : ''}">
                                <p class="text-sm">Cost Center Focus (e.g., IT, Service)</p>
                                <p class="text-xl font-mono text-red-600">Low ROI</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-green-100 shadow flex-1 ${index >= 6 ? 'border-4 border-green-500 pulse-animation' : ''}">
                                <p class="text-sm">Core Function Focus (Leaders)</p>
                                <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-700">2.1x ROI</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-semibold text-blue-600">High-Leverage Areas: Underwriting & Product Management</p>
                    </div>
                `;
            } else if (index >= 8 && index <= 11) {
                visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-blue-800 p-6 rounded-lg flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center text-white';
                
                const highlightClass = 'bg-yellow-400 text-blue-900 shadow-xl scale-105';
                const baseClass = 'bg-blue-600 text-white shadow-md';

                const pillar1 = index === 9 ? highlightClass : baseClass;
                const pillar2 = index === 10 ? highlightClass : baseClass;
                const pillar3 = index === 11 ? highlightClass : baseClass;
                
                visualContent = `
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Scaling AI: The Three Pillars</h3>
                    <div class="flex justify-around w-full max-w-lg space-x-3">
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center p-3 rounded-xl transition-all duration-300 ${pillar1}">
                            <p class="text-xl font-bold">1</p>
                            <p class="text-sm">Business Ownership</p>
                            <p class="text-xs opacity-75">(P&L Accountability)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center p-3 rounded-xl transition-all duration-300 ${pillar2}">
                            <p class="text-xl font-bold">2</p>
                            <p class="text-sm">Modern SaaS Foundation</p>
                            <p class="text-xs opacity-75">(Data Agility)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center p-3 rounded-xl transition-all duration-300 ${pillar3}">
                            <p class="text-xl font-bold">3</p>
                            <p class="text-sm">Human Augmentation</p>
                            <p class="text-xs opacity-75">(Model Governance)</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                `;
            } else if (index > 11) {
                 visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-gray-800 p-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center text-white';
                 visualContent = `
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h3 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-400">LEAD THE FUTURE.</h3>
                        <p class="text-xl">Stop Observing. Start Leading.</p>
                        <p class="text-lg mt-4 text-gray-400">Focus: P&L Impact, Business Ownership, SaaS Stack</p>
                    </div>
                 `;
            } else {
                visualContent = `<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-500">Visual: ${scene.visuals}</h2>`;
            }

            visualsPanel.innerHTML = visualContent;
            
            // Highlight current scene in the timeline
            document.querySelectorAll('#script-panel > div').forEach(el => {
                el.classList.remove('bg-blue-50', 'border-blue-600', 'shadow-lg');
                el.classList.add('bg-white', 'border-gray-200');
            });
            const currentEl = document.getElementById(`scene-${index}`);
            if (currentEl) {
                currentEl.classList.add('bg-blue-50', 'border-blue-600', 'shadow-lg');
                currentEl.classList.remove('bg-white', 'border-gray-200');
                currentEl.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
            }
        }

        // --- Core Simulation Logic ---

        function startSimulation() {
            if (isPlaying) return;
            isPlaying = true;
            statusText.textContent = 'Running...';
            statusText.classList.remove('text-red-500', 'text-green-500');
            statusText.classList.add('text-blue-500');
            
            playIcon.classList.add('hidden');
            pauseIcon.classList.remove('hidden');
            btnText.textContent = 'Pause Simulation';
            playPauseBtn.classList.remove('bg-green-600');
            playPauseBtn.classList.add('bg-yellow-600');

            // Find the correct starting scene index
            let nextSceneIndex = 0;
            for (let i = 0; i < scriptData.length; i++) {
                if (scriptData[i].time > simulationTime) {
                    nextSceneIndex = i;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (simulationTime === 0) nextSceneIndex = 0;
            
            // Set initial scene if starting from 0
            if (simulationTime === 0) updateScene(0);

            // Timer interval for updating time and progress
            intervalId = setInterval(() => {
                simulationTime++;
                updateProgress();

                // Check for next scene change
                const nextScene = scriptData[nextSceneIndex];
                if (nextScene && simulationTime >= nextScene.time) {
                    updateScene(nextSceneIndex);
                    nextSceneIndex++;
                }

                // End of simulation
                if (simulationTime >= totalDuration) {
                    pauseSimulation();
                    simulationTime = totalDuration;
                    updateProgress();
                    statusText.textContent = 'Completed!';
                    statusText.classList.remove('text-blue-500');
                    statusText.classList.add('text-green-500');
                }
            }, 1000); // Update every 1 second
        }

        function pauseSimulation() {
            if (!isPlaying) return;
            isPlaying = false;
            clearInterval(intervalId);
            statusText.textContent = 'Paused';
            statusText.classList.remove('text-blue-500', 'text-green-500');
            statusText.classList.add('text-red-500');
            
            playIcon.classList.remove('hidden');
            pauseIcon.classList.add('hidden');
            btnText.textContent = 'Resume Simulation';
            playPauseBtn.classList.remove('bg-yellow-600');
            playPauseBtn.classList.add('bg-green-600');
        }

        function resetSimulation() {
            pauseSimulation();
            simulationTime = 0;
            currentSceneIndex = -1;
            updateProgress();
            
            statusText.textContent = 'Ready';
            statusText.classList.remove('text-red-500', 'text-blue-500', 'text-green-500');
            
            voiceoverText.innerHTML = 'Press \'Play\' to start the module simulation.';
            visualsPanel.innerHTML = '<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-500">Video Stage: Waiting to Start...</h2>';
            visualsPanel.className = 'visuals-panel bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-center';
            
            playPauseBtn.classList.remove('bg-yellow-600');
            playPauseBtn.classList.add('bg-green-600');
            
            renderScriptTimeline();
        }

        // --- Event Listeners and Initialization ---

        playPauseBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            if (simulationTime >= totalDuration) {
                resetSimulation();
            } else if (isPlaying) {
                pauseSimulation();
            } else {
                startSimulation();
            }
        });

        resetBtn.addEventListener('click', resetSimulation);

        // Initial setup
        document.getElementById('total-time').textContent = formatTime(totalDuration);
        resetSimulation(); // Initial setup of state and visuals

    </script>
</body>
</html>
